<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3754] intermittent failure of org.apache.activemq.transport.vm.VmTransportNetworkBrokerTest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3754</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JUnit test org.apache.activemq.transport.vm.VmTransportNetworkBrokerTest fails most of the time on a Mac OSX machine. &lt;br/&gt;
The reason for the failure is that the test assumes the JVM itself will not create any additional threads at runtime. This however is a false assumption as on Mac OSX a daemon thread called &quot;Poller SunPKCS11-Darwin&quot; is created at some later point in time (after the test got kicked off already) under the main thread group. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This extra but JVM internal thread makes the test fail on Mac OSX right now.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
